race.comment: Good card assembled but grim predictions weather-wise which could have us on a wet track. Tricky start to proceedings with some of the country's most powerful stables producing some first-starts who have trialled impressively. TAUPE (11) is a half-sister to the speedy Tonkin who showed good speed to win her most recent jumpout when she was strong through the line under little urging. She looks primed for a big debut. REGAL RIPPER (4) also brings good jumpout form, and a wide gate, but many of the chances are drawn there which might help him blend into it. SPARKLING AWARD (10) unraced 3yo filly who has trialled twice. Impressive trial win on October 24 at Flemington over 800m. Profiles to play a role in the finish. ARABELLA STAR (12) is coming along well including placing in the latest Flemington jump-out. Raced just once last campaign and finished fifth at Randwick over 1000m. Respect any market moves.
